-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Vychan","type":"LAST","meanings":["Welsh: A Welsh name of great antiquity, from vyckan, little, small; i.e. small in stature. Compare the surname Bychan and the Armoric Le Bihan."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry ap Gwiliam Vychan was born about 1475, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Gwiliam Vychan, was 27 and his mother, Mrs. Gwiliam Vychan, was 27. He married Mrs. ap GWILIAM VYCHAN Henry about 1495, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters."},"et":{"Abt 1475–":"umbes 1475–Surnud","1475–Male":"1475–Surnud","1477–Female":"1477–Surnud","1490–1566":"1490–1566","1522–Female":"1522–Surnud","1450–Male":"1450–Surnud","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","Abt 1470":"umbes 1470","1522":"1522","1566":"1566","1477":"1477","Abt 1475":"umbes 1475","1475":"1475","Abt 1495":"umbes 1495","about 1522":"umbes 1522","1450":"1450","Abt 1490":"umbes 1490","1490":"1490","Griffith Gwyr, Priscedwyn, Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Griffith Gwyr Priscedwyn Glamorganshire Wales":"Gwyr, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1475–":"noin 1475–Kuollut","1475–Male":"1475–Kuollut"